==English==
===Etymology===
An alteration of Latin ''masturbat-'' (past participle stem of [[masturbari]] ‘masturbate’) apparently to resemble or provide overtones of [[manus]] ‘hand’ + [[stuprare]] ‘defile’.

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /mæstʊ'pɹeɪʃən/

===Noun===
'''mastupration'''
# [[masturbation]]
#:*'''1985''': She had caught him at the age of twelve in the act of '''mastupration'''.  Unseemly, unroman, Greekish, Jewish.  Well, in a sense he had done nothing but mastuprate since taking the purple. — Anthony Burgess, ''Kingdom of the Wicked''